cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) program and proposes a new paradigm in security research called Explainable Security (XSec). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it directly deals with security research. The paper also discusses AI techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. The paper proposes a new paradigm in security research, which involves reasoning about system models, threat models, and properties of security, privacy, and trust, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a likely category. The paper also discusses the different stakeholders involved in XSec, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a likely category. Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category.
